      <h1 align="center">Academic Visitors<br />
         at The Faculty of English</h1>
      <img src="images/senate.jpg" width="235" height="296" border="1" align="right" hspace="5" /> 
      <p>Before you apply to become an academic visitor with the Faculty, you 
        should read our information for academic visitors. This outlines what 
        <a href="facilities.htm">facilities</a> are available to a academic visitor, 
        <a href="apply.htm">how to apply</a>, <a href="fees.htm">fees and deposits</a>, 
        <a href="formalities.htm">formalities</a> (letter of recommendation and 
        requirements), <a href="visa.htm">visa procedure</a> and when is <a href="visiting.htm">the 
        best time to visit</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>To apply, you must send us</strong>: 
      </p><ul>
        <li>Your completed application form</li>
        <li>A letter of recommendation from your supervisor or Head of Department</li>
        <li>A clear indication of how you intend to pay the fees 
      </li></ul>
      <p>Once we have accepted you as an academic visitor, you need to submit 
        a deposit to us along with a plan with your <a href="accomodation.htm">accommodation 
        arrangements</a> while in Cambridge<br />
        <br />
        It should be noted that the Faculty of English is not concerned with the 
        <a href="efl.htm">teaching of the English language to non-native speakers</a>.</p>
      <p>In recent years, we have had academic visitors from Australia, China, 
        Ireland, Japan, South Africa, and Switzerland, and the Faculty of English 
        invites qualified senior scholars from overseas to be affiliated to the 
        Faculty during a short period of leave spent in Cambridge.</p>
      <p>Contact us on <a href="mailto:visitors@english.cam.ac.uk">visitors&#64;english.cam.ac.uk 
        </a>if you have any general enquiries about becoming a academic visitor.</p>
      <p>To obtain an application form, <a href="vs-application.pdf">download 
        the PDF application</a> form or write to:<br />
        <br />
        <em><strong>The Faculty of English</strong><br />
        9 West Road<br />
        Cambridge CB3 9DP<br />
        United Kingdom</em><br />
        Tel. 01223 335070<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:visitors&#64;english.cam.ac.uk">visitors&#64;english.cam.ac.uk 
        </a> </p>
